cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language interfaces to databases and follow-up query analysis. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also a likely category as the paper focuses on improving the performance of natural language interfaces to databases. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category as the paper proposes a novel approach that employs a ranking model with weakly supervised max-margin learning. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper deals with understanding the users' query intents and retrieving relevant information from databases. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a machine learning-based approach for follow-up query analysis.
